@startuml
title Request + failover sequences (local)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam maxMessageSize 120

actor User
participant "ui\nNext.js (browser)" as UI
participant "ui API routes\n(/api/* proxy)" as UIR
participant "router\nLB sim" as LB
participant "failover-controller" as FC
participant "api" as API
participant "postgres-primary\n(region-a)" as DBA
participant "postgres-replica\n(region-b)" as DBB
participant "infra\n(docker stats)\n(background)" as INFRA

== Steady state ==
note over DBA,DBB
Region A: primary (pg_is_in_recovery=false)
Region B: standby (pg_is_in_recovery=true)
Streaming replication active
end note

== A) Normal write flow (sync) ==
User -> UI : submit key/value
UI -> UIR : POST /api/write
UIR -> LB : POST /write
LB -> API : POST /write
API -> DBA : INSERT/UPDATE kv (commit)
API --> LB : 200 { row, region }
LB --> UIR : response
UIR --> UI : response
note over UI
UI updates Region A immediately
and refreshes dashboard
end note

== B) Read flow (sync) ==
UI -> UIR : GET /api/read?key=...
UIR -> LB : GET /read?key=...
LB -> API : GET /read?key=...
API -> DBA : SELECT (active region)
API --> LB : 200 { row, region }
LB --> UIR : response
UIR --> UI : response

== C) Background telemetry (async to UI) ==
UI -[#gray]-> UIR : GET /api/infra (periodic)
UIR -[#gray]-> INFRA : GET /infra (cached)
INFRA -[#gray]-> UIR : snapshot
UIR -[#gray]-> UI : snapshot (non-blocking)

== D) Automatic failover control loop ==
loop every CHECK_INTERVAL_SECONDS
  FC -> API : GET /decision
  API -> DBA : health/role checks
  API -> DBB : health + WAL caught_up/lag bytes
  API --> FC : decision { can_failover, checks, risk }
end

== Primary failure ==
User -> DBA : docker compose stop postgres-primary
note over DBA : container stopped / unreachable

note over FC
Controller only proceeds when:
- primary unreachable for N seconds
- replica healthy
- WAL caught up + lag OK
- no split brain
end note

== Promote + switch ==
FC -> DBB : pg_ctl promote
note over DBB : standby -> primary\n(pg_is_in_recovery=false)
FC -> API : POST /admin/switch?region=region-b
API --> FC : active_region=region-b

== After failover ==
note over DBA,DBB
Region B now primary and writable.
Replication is stopped; regions can diverge.
To restore A->B replication in this lab: reset volumes.
end note

@enduml

